515
00:33:18,537 --> 00:33:20,664
<i>You and Tara better watch your backs.</i>

516
00:33:20,748 --> 00:33:22,166
You better watch yours.

517
00:33:23,501 --> 00:33:24,460
No!

518
00:33:26,212 --> 00:33:27,630
Come on! Run!

519
00:33:29,340 --> 00:33:30,591
Come on!

520
00:33:30,674 --> 00:33:32,300
Help! Please!

521
00:33:32,384 --> 00:33:33,385
In there!

522
00:33:36,639 --> 00:33:37,765
Please help us!

523
00:33:37,848 --> 00:33:39,474
-We were just attacked.
-Call 911!

524
00:33:39,558 --> 00:33:41,059
There's a fucking line here, girls.

525
00:33:45,189 --> 00:33:46,690
You got a problem here, guy?

526
00:34:10,339 --> 00:34:12,466
-Go out the back!
-Thank you!

527
00:34:14,885 --> 00:34:17,679
-Fuck, it's locked.
-Keys! We need your keys!

528
00:34:20,099 --> 00:34:21,308
-Look out!
-Watch out!

529
00:34:26,564 --> 00:34:27,856
Wait.

530
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:29,733
Wait, wait! No, no, no!

531
00:36:07,748 --> 00:36:09,833
Run! Go! Run!

532
00:36:16,048 --> 00:36:17,716
-Going around back.
-Stay back there, ma'am.

533
00:36:43,242 --> 00:36:46,286
This was found next to the body
at the apartment crime scene.

534
00:36:47,329 --> 00:36:51,041
DNA says that it belonged
to someone named Richie Kirsch.

535
00:36:53,168 --> 00:36:54,419
Does that ring a bell?

536
00:36:56,714 --> 00:36:58,006
We're familiar with him.

537
00:36:58,090 --> 00:37:00,592
But the one that attacked us
had a different mask on.

538
00:37:01,510 --> 00:37:03,637
It was kind of more beat up.
Like it was older.

539
00:37:06,390 --> 00:37:07,391
I got to ask...

540
00:37:08,684 --> 00:37:10,268
do you have alibis for earlier tonight?

541
00:37:10,936 --> 00:37:12,771
I was at a party with my friends.

542
00:37:12,855 --> 00:37:14,231
I was at my therapist's.

543
00:37:14,732 --> 00:37:17,735
I can give you his information.
You can call to check if you want.

544
00:37:17,818 --> 00:37:19,444
And then I met Tara at that party

545
00:37:19,945 --> 00:37:21,237
where I tased someone.

546
00:37:22,448 --> 00:37:23,407
Unrelated.

547
00:37:25,117 --> 00:37:26,910
Was that before or after this happened?

548
00:37:26,994 --> 00:37:29,705
<i>-Murderer!
-What the fuck is wrong with you, bitch?</i>

549
00:37:29,788 --> 00:37:31,164
You got a problem with me?

550
00:37:31,248 --> 00:37:32,082
Before.

551
00:37:32,166 --> 00:37:34,459
The point is,
we were with people all night.

552
00:37:34,543 --> 00:37:36,795
So, our roommate's dad

553
00:37:37,546 --> 00:37:39,548
just happened to pull our case.

554
00:37:39,631 --> 00:37:42,050
-That'd be a crazy coincidence, right?
-Yeah.

555
00:37:42,134 --> 00:37:44,678
The detective who had the case
offered it to me

556
00:37:44,762 --> 00:37:46,346
because it involves Quinn.

557
00:37:47,181 --> 00:37:49,850
But I can totally give it back
if you're uncomfortable.

558
00:37:49,933 --> 00:37:50,934
It's up to you.

559
00:37:55,022 --> 00:37:56,023
It's fine.

560
00:37:56,982 --> 00:37:59,442
So if the man who attacked you
did steal your license

561
00:37:59,526 --> 00:38:00,985
and plant it next to the body...

562
00:38:02,237 --> 00:38:04,364
it'd probably be somebody close to you.

563
00:38:05,616 --> 00:38:07,451
How long have you known your friends?

564
00:38:07,534 --> 00:38:10,954
Well, we moved here with Mindy and Chad
for summer semester like six months ago.

565
00:38:12,164 --> 00:38:15,333
Quinn, Ethan, Anika-- all since then.

566
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:19,880
I think I can vouch for Quinn,
so that's one less we have to worry about.

567
00:38:20,506 --> 00:38:23,717
Do either of you have anyone
that might want to target you?

568
00:38:25,969 --> 00:38:27,261
Not anyone who's still alive.

569
00:38:27,971 --> 00:38:28,972
Yikes.

570
00:38:30,724 --> 00:38:33,059
<i>FBI's here, claiming jurisdiction.</i>

571
00:38:33,143 --> 00:38:34,102
Where are they?

572
00:38:40,651 --> 00:38:41,652
Can I help you?

573
00:38:44,696 --> 00:38:48,658
Special Agent Kirby Reed, FBI.
I work out of the Atlanta office.

574
00:38:48,742 --> 00:38:49,951
Oh. You lost?

575
00:38:51,620 --> 00:38:54,914
Your two vics were residents of my city
before they moved here for college.

576
00:38:54,998 --> 00:38:57,041
I have been investigating
their online activity

577
00:38:57,125 --> 00:38:58,668
for the past few months.

578
00:39:00,754 --> 00:39:01,880
Wow.

579
00:39:01,964 --> 00:39:03,048
Why?

580
00:39:03,131 --> 00:39:06,134
I take a special interest
in Ghostface attacks.

581
00:39:06,218 --> 00:39:07,928
-Kirby?
-Hey, Sam.

582
00:39:09,304 --> 00:39:10,305
What?

583
00:39:11,014 --> 00:39:12,015
Tara.

584
00:39:12,891 --> 00:39:13,975
You're the FBI?

585
00:39:14,852 --> 00:39:16,728
-You guys know each other?
-Yeah.

586
00:39:17,396 --> 00:39:20,232
We went to Woodsboro High together.
She was a senior when I was a freshman.

587
00:39:20,816 --> 00:39:22,734
We share a certain history, yeah.

588
00:39:23,777 --> 00:39:27,071
I'm not trying to get into
a jurisdictional pissing contest here,

589
00:39:27,155 --> 00:39:28,406
I just want to help.

590
00:39:29,032 --> 00:39:31,492
I'll show you mine... et cetera.

591
00:39:34,246 --> 00:39:35,247
Thank you.

592
00:39:36,540 --> 00:39:38,041
He left this mask at the bodega.

593
00:39:38,625 --> 00:39:40,251
DNA traces of two individuals,

594
00:39:40,335 --> 00:39:43,004
Charlie Walker, Jill Roberts,
both deceased.

595
00:39:43,964 --> 00:39:46,341
The Ghostface killers of 2011.

596
00:39:47,843 --> 00:39:50,095
Charlie Walker gave me this.

597
00:39:50,679 --> 00:39:52,347
Like I said, I take a special interest.

598
00:39:52,431 --> 00:39:54,975
Is this the mask he was wearing
when he attacked you?

599
00:39:55,934 --> 00:39:56,935
No.

600
00:39:57,519 --> 00:39:59,187
So he's leaving them on purpose.

601
00:39:59,271 --> 00:40:02,941
Which means whoever's doing this is
a student of the killers who came before.

602
00:40:03,025 --> 00:40:05,444
Maybe he believes
Sam is the latest in a long line.

603
00:40:06,445 --> 00:40:08,280
Yeah, good luck with that.

604
00:40:08,780 --> 00:40:09,989
We're getting out of town.

605
00:40:10,073 --> 00:40:11,866
I'm sorry, that's not possible.

606
00:40:12,576 --> 00:40:15,287
You're both persons of interest
in a double homicide,

607
00:40:15,370 --> 00:40:17,330
so you're not allowed to leave town.
Sorry.

608
00:40:17,414 --> 00:40:19,541
-Are you serious?
-He's right.

609
00:40:20,042 --> 00:40:22,169
-But if we work together--
-We're going.

610
00:40:25,797 --> 00:40:26,839
Here they come.

611
00:40:27,507 --> 00:40:30,384
Samantha, do you have an alibi
for last night's murders?

612
00:40:30,469 --> 00:40:32,429
Tara, do you feel safe around your sister?

613
00:40:32,512 --> 00:40:34,639
Tara! Tara!

614
00:40:34,723 --> 00:40:36,433
Gale Weathers, Channel 4.

615
00:40:37,559 --> 00:40:39,018
Do you ladies think you're the reason

616
00:40:39,102 --> 00:40:40,978
the Ghostface killer has come
to the Big Apple?

617
00:40:45,359 --> 00:40:48,153
Nice try, sweetie,
but I've done this dance before.

618
00:40:51,698 --> 00:40:53,199
-Stay away from us.
-Samantha!

619
00:40:54,076 --> 00:40:55,619
Are you still mad at me?

620
00:40:55,702 --> 00:40:58,413
You said you wouldn't write a book
about what happened.

621
00:40:58,497 --> 00:41:00,081
And then you wrote a book
about what happened.

622
00:41:00,165 --> 00:41:01,166
Oh, come on.

623
00:41:01,249 --> 00:41:04,126
Somebody was gonna write about it!
It's what I do.

624
00:41:04,211 --> 00:41:05,921
I heard you couldn't sell
the movie rights.

625
00:41:06,505 --> 00:41:09,591
It's all about true-crime limited series
these days.

626
00:41:09,675 --> 00:41:11,593
After everything we went through together.

627
00:41:12,427 --> 00:41:13,428
What would Dewey think?

628
00:41:15,931 --> 00:41:17,891
-That's a low blow.
-So was your book.

629
00:41:18,475 --> 00:41:21,144
You called me "unstable"
and a "born killer".

630
00:41:21,228 --> 00:41:23,230
That's taken out of context.

631
00:41:23,313 --> 00:41:24,439
That's literally a quote.

632
00:41:24,523 --> 00:41:26,483
You don't think what you wrote
has something to do with

633
00:41:26,566 --> 00:41:28,109
what's happening to us?

634
00:41:28,193 --> 00:41:29,569
Come on.

635
00:41:30,195 --> 00:41:32,030
Hey, I talked to Sidney.

636
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:37,035
-She's not coming here, is she?
-No.

637
00:41:37,536 --> 00:41:40,830
She sends her love, but she's taking Mark
and the kids someplace safe.

638
00:41:41,373 --> 00:41:43,625
She deserves to have her happy ending.

639
00:41:45,544 --> 00:41:46,962
On that much, we agree.

640
00:41:48,296 --> 00:41:51,007
Hey, I want to catch this fucker
as much as you do!

641
00:41:51,091 --> 00:41:52,092
Maybe.

642
00:41:53,051 --> 00:41:55,303
Or maybe you're just afraid
that without Ghostface in your life,

643
00:41:55,387 --> 00:41:56,888
you're gonna fade away.

644
00:42:04,229 --> 00:42:06,397
You fools! You're in danger!

645
00:42:06,481 --> 00:42:10,818
Can't you see? They're after you!
They're after all of us!

646
00:42:10,902 --> 00:42:13,237
Our wives, our children, everyone!

647
00:42:13,321 --> 00:42:16,782
They're here already! You're next!

648
00:42:17,576 --> 00:42:22,076
You're next! You're next! You're next!
You're next!

649
00:42:31,673 --> 00:42:32,674
Who is it?

650
00:42:49,524 --> 00:42:53,194
You're a day early for trick-or-treating,
you know.

651
00:43:33,485 --> 00:43:35,778
Okay, nerds, listen up!

652
00:43:36,446 --> 00:43:38,239
As terrifying as this all is,

653
00:43:38,323 --> 00:43:40,491
I'm actually glad I get a chance
to redeem myself

654
00:43:40,575 --> 00:43:43,244
for not calling the killers last time.

655
00:43:43,745 --> 00:43:45,913
-Yep.
-It's fine. Okay.

656
00:43:45,997 --> 00:43:49,667
The way I see it, someone is out
to make a sequel to the requel.

657
00:43:50,335 --> 00:43:51,336
What's a requel?

658
00:43:52,045 --> 00:43:54,505
You're beautiful, sweetie.
Let's hold questions to the end.

659
00:43:54,589 --> 00:43:56,424
Stab 7 took place in Woodsboro.

660
00:43:57,134 --> 00:43:59,386
Stab 2 took place in college.

661
00:43:59,469 --> 00:44:01,762
So we think that the killer is trying
to copy the movies?

662
00:44:01,847 --> 00:44:03,348
That is one possibility.

663
00:44:03,431 --> 00:44:05,558
Heroes now in college: Check.

664
00:44:05,642 --> 00:44:08,478
Suspicious new characters brought in
to round out the suspect list

665
00:44:08,562 --> 00:44:09,563
and/or body count:

666
00:44:09,646 --> 00:44:11,731
-Check, check and check.
-I don't like this.

667
00:44:11,815 --> 00:44:14,234
<i>-But it can't just be about Stab 2.
-Why not?</i>

668
00:44:14,317 --> 00:44:17,028
It would make sense
if this were just a sequel.

669
00:44:17,112 --> 00:44:20,657
But we're not in a sequel,
because nobody just makes sequels anymore.

670
00:44:23,201 --> 00:44:24,785
We're in a franchise!

671
00:44:24,870 --> 00:44:28,373
And there are certain rules
to a continuing franchise.

672
00:44:28,456 --> 00:44:30,499
-I had a feeling.
-Rule one:

673
00:44:30,584 --> 00:44:32,210
Everything is bigger than last time.

674
00:44:32,294 --> 00:44:35,213
Bigger budget, bigger cast,
bigger body count.

675
00:44:35,297 --> 00:44:37,090
Longer chases, shoot-outs, beheadings.

676
00:44:37,174 --> 00:44:39,176
You got to top what came before
to keep people coming back.

677
00:44:39,259 --> 00:44:41,219
-Beheadings?
-Beheadings.

678
00:44:41,303 --> 00:44:44,764
Rule two: Whatever happened last time,
expect the opposite.

679
00:44:44,848 --> 00:44:47,809
Franchises only survive
by subverting expectations.

680
00:44:47,893 --> 00:44:50,979
If the killers last time
were whiny snowflake film nerds

681
00:44:51,062 --> 00:44:53,064
with Letterboxd accounts
instead of personalities,

682
00:44:53,148 --> 00:44:55,608
you can bet
the opposite will be true here.

683
00:44:56,151 --> 00:44:58,736
And rule three: No one is safe.

684
00:44:59,654 --> 00:45:02,239
Legacy characters?
Cannon fodder at this point.

685
00:45:02,324 --> 00:45:06,536
Usually brought back only to be killed off
in some cheap bid for nostalgia.

686
00:45:06,620 --> 00:45:09,247
It's not looking too good
for Gale and Kirby.

687
00:45:09,331 --> 00:45:11,416
Oh, and that's not even the worst part!

688
00:45:11,499 --> 00:45:13,584
This is the part
where she tells us the worst part.

689
00:45:13,668 --> 00:45:15,169
The worst part is,

690
00:45:15,253 --> 00:45:19,753
franchises are just continuing episodic
installments designed to boost an IP.

691
00:45:20,425 --> 00:45:24,887
Which means main characters
are completely expendable now, too.

692
00:45:24,971 --> 00:45:28,349
Laurie Strode, Nancy Thompson,
Ellen Ripley,

693
00:45:28,433 --> 00:45:31,269
Sally Hardesty, Jigsaw, Tony Stark,
James Bond...

694
00:45:31,353 --> 00:45:35,690
I mean, even Luke Skywalker! All died
so their franchises could live on.

695
00:45:36,191 --> 00:45:38,234
That means it's not just the friend group.

696
00:45:38,318 --> 00:45:41,070
Any of us could go at any time,

697
00:45:41,947 --> 00:45:43,657
especially Sam and Tara.

698
00:45:45,659 --> 00:45:47,994
-Wait, any of us?
-Yeah.

699
00:45:48,078 --> 00:45:50,789
-Am I in the friend group?
-Yeah.

700
00:45:50,872 --> 00:45:53,082
Am I one of the targets?

701
00:45:54,542 --> 00:45:56,043
Am I gonna die a virgin?

702
00:45:57,879 --> 00:45:59,422
That was a weird over share.

703
00:45:59,506 --> 00:46:01,674
But it brings us to our current suspects:

704
00:46:02,300 --> 00:46:03,301
Ethan.

705
00:46:03,385 --> 00:46:07,013
The shy, dorky guy who no one suspects
because he's so shy and dorky.

706
00:46:07,097 --> 00:46:11,101
Why am I on the suspect list?
Because I'm randomly Chad's roommate?

707
00:46:11,184 --> 00:46:13,019
Roommate lotteries can be juked.

708
00:46:13,103 --> 00:46:15,271
You could have fixed it to get next to us.

709
00:46:15,355 --> 00:46:16,522
Quinn.

710
00:46:16,606 --> 00:46:19,775
The slutty roommate.
A horror movie classic.

711
00:46:19,859 --> 00:46:22,611
"Sex positive," but thank you?

712
00:46:23,905 --> 00:46:25,781
How did you come to live
with Sam and Tara?

713
00:46:25,865 --> 00:46:28,075
I answered their ad online.

714
00:46:28,159 --> 00:46:31,537
Okay, say no more.
You've already implicated yourself enough.

715
00:46:31,621 --> 00:46:33,289
It was an anonymous ad, Mindy.

716
00:46:33,373 --> 00:46:35,625
And you know we vetted her.
Plus her dad is a cop.

717
00:46:35,709 --> 00:46:37,585
And that makes it more likely
that she's the killer,

718
00:46:37,669 --> 00:46:39,295
because having a cop dad is a great cover.

719
00:46:39,379 --> 00:46:41,672
Do you not remember
how these movies work, Tara?

720
00:46:42,465 --> 00:46:44,216
Is she always like this?

721
00:46:44,301 --> 00:46:46,428
And finally, Anika.

722
00:46:48,847 --> 00:46:50,557
Never trust the love interest.

723
00:46:53,351 --> 00:46:57,605
Okay! So, we have our rules
and we have our suspects.

724
00:46:57,689 --> 00:46:59,399
But wait. What about you guys?

725
00:46:59,983 --> 00:47:02,777
I think it's pretty safe to rule out
the four of us

726
00:47:02,861 --> 00:47:04,487
who went through this last year
in Woodsboro.

727
00:47:05,280 --> 00:47:07,282
-Agreed.
-Not agreed.

728
00:47:07,365 --> 00:47:11,865
What if the trauma you all went through
caused one or more of you to snap?

729
00:47:12,620 --> 00:47:14,997
Yeah, or the fame you got
from the killings

730
00:47:15,081 --> 00:47:16,540
made you thirsty for more.

731
00:47:16,624 --> 00:47:20,586
I mean, let's be honest here, some
of the theories online about Sam are--

732
00:47:20,670 --> 00:47:22,213
Don't you fucking dare.

733
00:47:22,881 --> 00:47:25,049
Okay, she's right, though.

734
00:47:25,133 --> 00:47:26,134
I mean, face facts,

735
00:47:26,217 --> 00:47:28,302
if we're all suspects,
you're all suspects.

736
00:47:37,354 --> 00:47:40,732
Remember Samantha Carpenter's alibi,
the therapist?

737
00:47:41,608 --> 00:47:43,901
He was stabbed to death. Through the nose.

738
00:47:45,028 --> 00:47:47,447
Through the nose. How messed up is that?

739
00:47:47,530 --> 00:47:48,989
It's pretty messed up.

740
00:47:50,116 --> 00:47:53,452
He turned her in for making
threatening remarks, ended up dead.

741
00:47:53,953 --> 00:47:56,080
And guess which patient's
notes were stolen?

742
00:47:57,624 --> 00:48:00,335
So Sam kills her own alibi
and steals her own session notes?

743
00:48:01,044 --> 00:48:02,086
Maybe.

744
00:48:03,296 --> 00:48:04,714
Another mask was found at the scene.

745
00:48:05,715 --> 00:48:07,425
It's a DNA match for Roman Bridger.

746
00:48:08,009 --> 00:48:10,344
The Ghostface who was directing Stab 3.

747
00:48:11,888 --> 00:48:15,016
It's like he's leaving us
real-life franchise Easter eggs.

748
00:48:15,100 --> 00:48:18,311
Like dropping
the killers' masks in reverse.

749
00:48:19,312 --> 00:48:21,314
Almost like he's counting down
to something.

750
00:48:22,482 --> 00:48:24,025
What happens when he gets to one?

751
00:48:29,114 --> 00:48:32,117
So we've had
nine Ghostface killers so far.

752
00:48:32,200 --> 00:48:33,576
Nine. But I thought in the movies--

753
00:48:33,660 --> 00:48:35,536
Forget about the movies.
The movies don't matter.

754
00:48:36,704 --> 00:48:39,707
Look. Last year
was Amber Freeman and Richie Kirsch,

755
00:48:39,791 --> 00:48:41,667
whose masks we found
at the first crime scene

756
00:48:41,751 --> 00:48:45,254
along with the bodies of two film students
who killed their professor

757
00:48:45,338 --> 00:48:46,464
earlier the same night.

758
00:48:46,965 --> 00:48:51,260
Then it was Jill Roberts
and Charlie Walker-- theirs at the bodega.

759
00:48:51,344 --> 00:48:53,929
Roman Bridger was the only
single Ghostface.

760
00:48:54,013 --> 00:48:55,389
Kudos to him for ambition.

761
00:48:55,473 --> 00:48:57,766
His mask was found at the shrink's.

762
00:48:57,851 --> 00:49:01,437
Which just leaves Mickey Altieri,
