01:06:22,227 --> 01:06:25,521
The killer must have found this place
before he murdered Jason and Greg.

1014
01:06:25,606 --> 01:06:28,650
And then he took the masks
off the mannequins.

1015
01:06:28,734 --> 01:06:31,862
All nine, from Stu and Billy
to Amber and Richie.

1016
01:06:57,596 --> 01:07:00,807
Hot damn! How fucking cool is this place?

1017
01:07:00,891 --> 01:07:02,225
Fuck, no.

1018
01:07:02,309 --> 01:07:03,393
Fuck, yes.

1019
01:07:04,019 --> 01:07:08,189
Come on, Sam, you got to be excited
to get our murder on again. Together.

1020
01:07:08,273 --> 01:07:10,900
Billy and Sam. Team Loomis.

1021
01:07:11,985 --> 01:07:14,070
Get ready to slice up more motherfuckers.

1022
01:07:25,249 --> 01:07:26,250
What are you doing?

1023
01:07:31,338 --> 01:07:32,630
I don't know.

1024
01:07:37,135 --> 01:07:38,219
So,

1025
01:07:38,929 --> 01:07:41,181
somebody killed these chuckle fucks

1026
01:07:42,641 --> 01:07:43,933
and took over?

1027
01:07:44,017 --> 01:07:46,644
Someone who believes
that Sam masterminded Woodsboro.

1028
01:07:46,728 --> 01:07:49,981
If this were a normal Stab movie,
this would be the killer's lair.

1029
01:07:50,482 --> 01:07:52,734
<i>Which means
this isn't a normal Stab movie.</i>

1030
01:08:08,792 --> 01:08:11,586
The TV that killed Stu Macher.

1031
01:08:11,670 --> 01:08:13,254
If you believe he's dead.

1032
01:08:15,424 --> 01:08:17,259
I hear you're a horror fan.

1033
01:08:18,093 --> 01:08:19,344
It's been said.

1034
01:08:20,929 --> 01:08:22,847
Best Nightmare on Elm Street?

1035
01:08:22,931 --> 01:08:23,932
The original.

1036
01:08:24,516 --> 01:08:26,309
Best Friday the 13th?

1037
01:08:26,393 --> 01:08:27,644
<i>-Part II.
-The Final Chapter.</i>

1038
01:08:29,396 --> 01:08:30,772
Had a crush on Corey Feldman.

1039
01:08:30,856 --> 01:08:32,524
Okay. Respect.

1040
01:08:33,817 --> 01:08:34,818
<i>Psycho II </i> is...

1041
01:08:34,901 --> 01:08:36,027
-underrated.
-underrated.

1042
01:08:37,237 --> 01:08:40,156
Candyman. The original or requel?

1043
01:08:40,240 --> 01:08:41,157
-Both.
-Both.

1044
01:08:42,659 --> 01:08:44,827
Okay. Okay.

1045
01:08:44,911 --> 01:08:46,495
Game recognize game.

1046
01:08:53,712 --> 01:08:54,713
You okay?

1047
01:08:57,966 --> 01:09:00,259
Sam, when do I get
to be a normal person again?

1048
01:09:03,347 --> 01:09:04,348
I don't know.

1049
01:09:04,931 --> 01:09:06,599
I don't want to be a part of this.

1050
01:09:07,893 --> 01:09:10,186
I don't want to be a part
of some stupid legacy because I'm--

1051
01:09:10,270 --> 01:09:11,396
Because of me.

1052
01:09:14,107 --> 01:09:15,108
I'm sorry.

1053
01:09:16,360 --> 01:09:17,569
Just drop it, Sam.

1054
01:09:19,446 --> 01:09:20,447
Tara.

1055
01:09:21,365 --> 01:09:22,324
I got her.

1056
01:09:27,329 --> 01:09:28,747
That seemed intense.

1057
01:09:30,207 --> 01:09:32,751
Ever since I came back into her life,
I've just...

1058
01:09:35,671 --> 01:09:37,089
made a mess of it.

1059
01:09:37,673 --> 01:09:38,674
Hey.

1060
01:09:38,757 --> 01:09:40,341
Where's your mother in all this?

1061
01:09:41,051 --> 01:09:44,095
She cut me off
when I told Tara about Billy.

1062
01:09:45,013 --> 01:09:48,349
Then Tara cut her off
because she wouldn't talk to me,

1063
01:09:49,184 --> 01:09:51,477
SO now neither of us have a mother.

1064
01:09:51,561 --> 01:09:53,896
I'm sorry to say this, but fuck her.

1065
01:09:54,731 --> 01:09:56,149
My parents sucked, too.

1066
01:09:57,984 --> 01:09:59,986
But you can still make your own family.

1067
01:10:00,862 --> 01:10:02,697
Even if it's just with one person.

1068
01:10:06,868 --> 01:10:08,828
And if you lose that one person?

1069
01:10:11,289 --> 01:10:12,832
You just keep going.

1070
01:10:14,167 --> 01:10:17,545
And maybe you find another loner,
and you look after each other.

1071
01:10:26,054 --> 01:10:28,014
How'd you get past what happened to you?

1072
01:10:33,437 --> 01:10:35,355
I almost died after I was stabbed.

1073
01:10:37,190 --> 01:10:38,691
Technically, I did die.

1074
01:10:38,775 --> 01:10:40,276
For four minutes.

1075
01:10:43,405 --> 01:10:44,572
When I recovered...

1076
01:10:46,408 --> 01:10:47,409
I got mad.

1077
01:10:48,326 --> 01:10:51,495
I didn't want to spend the rest
of my life being afraid of monsters.

1078
01:10:53,248 --> 01:10:55,750
I wanted the monsters to be afraid of me.

1079
01:10:57,043 --> 01:10:58,377
I like that.

1080
01:10:59,337 --> 01:11:00,629
Sorry to interrupt.

1081
01:11:01,715 --> 01:11:04,884
Think I might have an idea about how
to turn the tables on this creep.

1082
01:11:04,968 --> 01:11:05,969
Yeah. We're in.

1083
01:11:06,678 --> 01:11:08,638
Sorry, Gale. No press allowed.

1084
01:11:08,722 --> 01:11:10,849
Police business. I'm good at my job, too.

1085
01:11:17,773 --> 01:11:19,274
You should have stayed with the others.

1086
01:11:19,900 --> 01:11:20,901
That's not gonna happen.

1087
01:11:21,777 --> 01:11:24,654
There's no point in both of us
putting ourselves at risk.

1088
01:11:24,738 --> 01:11:27,240
I'm not. I'm your backup.

1089
01:11:31,745 --> 01:11:35,665
So we're really doing the phone tracing
thing that never works in the movies.

1090
01:11:35,749 --> 01:11:38,835
It'll be all, "Keep him talking, Sam.
Two more minutes, I've almost got him."

1091
01:11:38,919 --> 01:11:41,504
And then he hangs up just
before we can get a lock.

1092
01:11:41,588 --> 01:11:45,049
I can trace a call in under 15 seconds.

1093
01:11:47,427 --> 01:11:50,430
Well, you've got them out there as bait.

1094
01:11:50,514 --> 01:11:52,599
Because the killer usually calls
from somewhere nearby.

1095
01:11:52,682 --> 01:11:55,976
And you think they're safe because
it's broad daylight in a public place?

1096
01:11:56,061 --> 01:11:58,396
Look, I am here, okay? And so is Bailey.

1097
01:11:58,480 --> 01:12:01,107
This is exactly how our Uncle Randy died.

1098
01:12:01,191 --> 01:12:02,901
Broad daylight. Public place.

1099
01:12:02,984 --> 01:12:05,903
Yanked into a van.
Stab, stab, stab. No more Randy.

1100
01:12:11,827 --> 01:12:15,038
Hey, Sam? Stay frosty out there, okay?

1101
01:12:15,121 --> 01:12:16,122
We're good.

1102
01:12:39,938 --> 01:12:43,232
-You're gonna die, you know.
-No, you're gonna die, Samantha!

1103
01:12:43,316 --> 01:12:46,902
Choking on your own blood
while I hack up your sister.

1104
01:12:48,280 --> 01:12:49,614
Unless we find you first.

1105
01:12:49,698 --> 01:12:52,826
For a mastermind, you're not very bright.

1106
01:12:52,909 --> 01:12:57,330
Waiting for me to call, desperately hoping
I'm nearby so the police can grab me?

1107
01:13:00,250 --> 01:13:03,378
But I'm not nearby. I'm a step ahead.

1108
01:13:03,962 --> 01:13:06,214
Be seeing you, Samantha.

1109
01:13:08,174 --> 01:13:09,049
Did you get it?

1110
01:13:09,134 --> 01:13:12,387
Yep. Geolocation coming through right now.

1111
01:13:14,389 --> 01:13:15,890
He's on the Upper West Side.

1112
01:13:15,974 --> 01:13:19,227
He's inside an apartment building,
halfway across the city.

1113
01:13:19,311 --> 01:13:21,730
-On West 96th?
-How did you know that?

1114
01:13:25,567 --> 01:13:26,776
Gale.

1115
01:13:28,695 --> 01:13:29,696
"No press."

1116
01:13:29,779 --> 01:13:32,948
Bitch, last time I saw you,
you were in glee club.

1117
01:13:33,617 --> 01:13:35,994
Forgive me if I don't trust you
to keep them safe.

1118
01:13:36,077 --> 01:13:37,787
-Here you go, baby.
-Thanks.

1119
01:13:38,538 --> 01:13:41,374
My friend Danny works on the
Upper West Side. He can get there quicker.

1120
01:13:41,458 --> 01:13:44,419
Yeah, or he could finish her off.
Is it possible he's the killer?

1121
01:13:44,502 --> 01:13:46,170
Fuck. We have to get there now.

1122
01:13:46,254 --> 01:13:48,464
It's 50 blocks away. We don't even know
if it's true. Sam, wait!

1123
01:13:48,548 --> 01:13:50,132
-Take a minute.
-We don't have a minute.

1124
01:13:50,216 --> 01:13:52,092
You have to trust me,
we got to make the right call.

1125
01:13:52,177 --> 01:13:53,636
-He's already--
-Sam!

1126
01:13:54,429 --> 01:13:55,471
Get in.

1127
01:13:55,555 --> 01:13:56,722
What's she doing?

1128
01:13:56,806 --> 01:13:58,682
Hey, get out of my car!

1129
01:13:59,476 --> 01:14:01,561
What do you think you're doing?
That's an official vehicle!

1130
01:14:01,645 --> 01:14:02,646
Should we use the sirens?

1131
01:14:02,729 --> 01:14:05,189
Did you think we'd steal a police car
and not use the sirens?

1132
01:14:05,273 --> 01:14:06,857
-Do you even have a license?
-Fuck, yeah.

1133
01:14:06,942 --> 01:14:08,193
What are you doing?

1134
01:14:09,069 --> 01:14:11,654
It's a cop car! You can't steal a cop car!

1135
01:14:14,824 --> 01:14:15,950
That'll be our food.

1136
01:14:18,745 --> 01:14:19,746
Hello?

1137
01:14:20,997 --> 01:14:22,456
Not the food. It's for you.

1138
01:14:23,541 --> 01:14:24,625
Who is it?

1139
01:14:24,709 --> 01:14:26,127
May I ask who's calling, please?

1140
01:14:28,213 --> 01:14:29,505
He says it's the killer.

1141
01:14:37,013 --> 01:14:39,473
-Hello?
-Hello, Gale.

1142
01:14:39,557 --> 01:14:42,476
Strange that you and I have never spoken
on the phone.

1143
01:14:43,061 --> 01:14:44,812
This is long overdue.

1144
01:14:45,397 --> 01:14:46,398
I agree.

1145
01:14:46,898 --> 01:14:48,065
Call the police.

1146
01:14:48,149 --> 01:14:49,650
[ Figured after all these years...

1147
01:14:51,069 --> 01:14:52,904
...you'd want an interview.

1148
01:14:53,571 --> 01:14:55,781
Well, you figured right.

1149
01:14:57,575 --> 01:14:59,618
So, what's your motive this time?

1150
01:15:00,620 --> 01:15:03,706
You angry at the movies
or you just trying to stay relevant?

1151
01:15:03,790 --> 01:15:05,917
I could ask you the same.

1152
01:15:06,001 --> 01:15:09,546
Don't you know
the legacy characters are disposable now?

1153
01:15:09,629 --> 01:15:12,089
Nobody cares about last century's heroes.

1154
01:15:12,173 --> 01:15:15,509
-Then why bother with me at all?
-Call it nostalgia.

1155
01:15:15,593 --> 01:15:17,469
Or maybe you deserve to be punished

1156
01:15:17,554 --> 01:15:20,098
for all that money you made
off the misery of others.

1157
01:15:20,598 --> 01:15:25,098
Maybe it's time
someone made a buck reporting your death.

1158
01:15:25,520 --> 01:15:27,939
You know you're like the tenth guy
to try this, right?

1159
01:15:28,773 --> 01:15:30,065
And spoiler alert,

1160
01:15:30,900 --> 01:15:33,736
it never works out for the dipshit
in the mask.

1161
01:15:35,697 --> 01:15:38,574
Oh, but they certainly leave a mark
before they go, don't they?

1162
01:15:39,075 --> 01:15:42,203
Richie and Amber managed to butcher Dewey.

1163
01:15:42,287 --> 01:15:44,998
Carved him up like a Christmas goose.

1164
01:15:45,498 --> 01:15:49,418
How does it feel to lose the only man
who ever loved you?

1165
01:15:49,502 --> 01:15:50,794
Fuck you!

1166
01:15:50,879 --> 01:15:54,841
<i>How does it feel to know
that you weren't there for him at the end?</i>

1167
01:15:55,717 --> 01:15:58,511
<i>Not there to give him comfort</i>

1168
01:15:58,595 --> 01:16:01,139
as he died screaming in his own guts.

1169
01:16:01,222 --> 01:16:03,432
You're the one who's gonna die screaming.

1170
01:16:03,516 --> 01:16:07,019
<i>Maybe. But you won't be around to see it.</i>

1171
01:16:07,103 --> 01:16:09,313
<i>You couldn't stop what happened to Dewey.</i>

1172
01:16:09,397 --> 01:16:11,941
<i>Just like you're not gonna be able
to stop this.</i>

1173
01:16:48,186 --> 01:16:49,520
Oh, God!

1174
01:17:13,962 --> 01:17:16,673
How's that for nostalgia, fucker?

1175
01:17:29,561 --> 01:17:30,770
You missed.

1176
01:17:31,271 --> 01:17:32,647
Sure I did.

1177
01:17:32,730 --> 01:17:35,649
You win. I'm in the elevator heading
for the ground floor.

1178
01:17:36,609 --> 01:17:37,860
Sure you are.

1179
01:17:41,739 --> 01:17:44,408
Maybe you did hit me. Maybe I'm wounded.

1180
01:17:45,243 --> 01:17:47,745
<i>Or maybe I'm wearing a bulletproof vest.</i>

1181
01:17:48,246 --> 01:17:50,831
That's why I'm gonna shoot you
in the fucking head!

1182
01:18:03,720 --> 01:18:06,347
You would've made a good killer, Gale.

1183
01:18:06,848 --> 01:18:09,600
Sidney never would've made sense
and Dewey was the fan favorite.

1184
01:18:09,684 --> 01:18:12,061
But you cracking under the pressure

1185
01:18:12,145 --> 01:18:15,690
and turning into Ghostface
would've been a great twist.

1186
01:18:15,773 --> 01:18:17,316
Keep talking, asshole.

1187
01:18:18,651 --> 01:18:21,945
<i>Sure. What do you want to talk about?</i>

1188
01:18:25,033 --> 01:18:27,452
You never got to be the leading lady,
did you?

1189
01:18:27,535 --> 01:18:32,035
It was always all about poor sweet Sidney,
sucking up all the oxygen.

1190
01:18:32,749 --> 01:18:34,459
What did that leave you to be?

1191
01:18:34,959 --> 01:18:36,502
The brains and the sex appeal.

1192
01:18:38,004 --> 01:18:39,588
Sorry about your boyfriend.

1193
01:18:40,256 --> 01:18:43,175
All those muscles didn't help much.

1194
01:18:43,259 --> 01:18:44,260
They sure didn't.

1195
01:18:47,388 --> 01:18:48,555
Can you hold, please?

1196
01:20:13,057 --> 01:20:14,308
Fuck you!

1197
01:20:14,851 --> 01:20:15,810
Hey, fuckface!

1198
01:20:21,649 --> 01:20:23,192
Gale!

1199
01:20:24,110 --> 01:20:25,736
Oh, shit. Gale?

1200
01:20:27,071 --> 01:20:28,280
Gale.

1201
01:20:30,241 --> 01:20:31,450
Sorry.

1202
01:20:31,534 --> 01:20:32,535
I'm sorry.

1203
01:20:34,287 --> 01:20:36,163
I should've known
that he was gonna come after you.

1204
01:20:36,247 --> 01:20:37,331
I'm so sorry.

1205
01:20:39,292 --> 01:20:40,626
He didn't get me.

1206
01:20:43,254 --> 01:20:44,296
Tell Sidney

1207
01:20:45,340 --> 01:20:46,966
he never got me.

1208
01:20:52,638 --> 01:20:53,639
Gale?

1209
01:20:56,309 --> 01:20:57,643
-Gale.
-Gale.

1210
01:20:57,727 --> 01:20:59,520
Gale? Please.

1211
01:20:59,604 --> 01:21:00,646
Out of the way!

1212
01:21:00,730 --> 01:21:03,983
-Out of the way!
-Move. You got to move. Move!

1213
01:21:04,067 --> 01:21:05,276
No! No!

1214
01:21:06,194 --> 01:21:07,653
-Get them back.
-Sam, please!

1215
01:21:07,737 --> 01:21:09,989
-They need to move now.
-Please step back.

1216
01:21:11,115 --> 01:21:12,783
-Call it in.
-Right away.

1217
01:21:14,702 --> 01:21:16,537
-Checking.
-Come on, Gale.

1218
01:21:20,249 --> 01:21:22,417
Got a weak pulse. Get the backboard.

1219
01:21:22,502 --> 01:21:23,503
We need to move now.

1220
01:21:27,465 --> 01:21:29,508
Backboard! Let's move.

1221
01:21:44,941 --> 01:21:46,442
I got here as fast as I could.

1222
01:21:48,611 --> 01:21:49,820
Did you?

1223
01:21:51,531 --> 01:21:53,282
I'm scared, you guys.

1224
01:21:53,366 --> 01:21:55,242
I really don't want to get hurt again.

1225
01:21:56,285 --> 01:21:57,286
Neither do I.

1226
01:21:59,038 --> 01:22:00,622
I don't want you
getting hurt again, either.

1227
01:22:00,706 --> 01:22:02,541
I know. I know.

1228
01:22:08,631 --> 01:22:09,965
So what do we do now?

1229
01:22:11,884 --> 01:22:13,844
Maybe he gets to win this time.

1230
01:22:17,265 --> 01:22:19,225
He wants to punish me.

1231
01:22:22,019 --> 01:22:23,020
Me.

1232
01:22:24,981 --> 01:22:26,273
So maybe I let him.

1233
01:22:27,358 --> 01:22:29,568
I'll just give myself up.

1234
01:22:30,862 --> 01:22:32,697
If this is what I have to do

1235
01:22:33,865 --> 01:22:35,324
to keep you safe...

1236
01:22:36,742 --> 01:22:37,743
it's worth it.

1237
01:22:37,827 --> 01:22:39,787
No, we're not doing that, Sam.

1238
01:22:39,871 --> 01:22:42,248
You went back to Woodsboro to protect me.

1239
01:22:42,331 --> 01:22:44,833
Every single day,
you make the decision to protect me.

1240
01:22:44,917 --> 01:22:47,628
None of us would even be alive
if it weren't for you.

1241
01:22:48,379 --> 01:22:50,547
You have to let us protect you this time.

1242
01:22:51,215 --> 01:22:52,299
-No.
-Yes.

1243
01:22:54,302 --> 01:22:55,303
We're a team, remember?

1244
01:22:55,386 --> 01:22:56,678
Actually...

1245
01:22:58,389 --> 01:22:59,390
we're a family.

1246
01:22:59,474 --> 01:23:02,268
Let's go! Core Four! Come on.

1247
01:23:02,351 --> 01:23:03,894
-Core Four.
-Come on.

1248
01:23:03,978 --> 01:23:05,479
-Core what?
-It's an us thing.

1249
01:23:07,565 --> 01:23:09,441
He's gonna keep coming after us.

1250
01:23:10,318 --> 01:23:12,945
Isn't there somewhere
that's safe we could just hole up in?

1251
01:23:13,029 --> 01:23:14,739
No, he's just gonna keep finding us.

1252
01:23:15,448 --> 01:23:16,490
Great.

1253
01:23:18,951 --> 01:23:19,993
We could use that, though.

1254
01:23:23,080 --> 01:23:25,832
I'm getting my ass chewed out
for not dropping the case

1255
01:23:25,917 --> 01:23:27,043
and now you want me to do what?

1256
01:23:27,126 --> 01:23:29,711
We want to lure him to a secure location
and trap him inside.

1257
01:23:31,422 --> 01:23:32,631
And then what?

1258
01:23:33,716 --> 01:23:34,717
We execute him.

1259
01:23:40,348 --> 01:23:41,557
Are you gonna help us?

1260
01:23:44,519 --> 01:23:46,103
Let's kill the son of a bitch.

1261
